      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/furszy/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Currently, if users provide a non-boolean convertible value to a negated option,\r\nsuch as '-nowallet=not_a_boolean', the initialization process results in a fatal\r\nerror, causing an unclean shutdown and displaying a poorly descriptive error\r\nmessage:\r\n\"JSON value of type bool is not of expected type string.\" (On bitcoind. The GUI\r\ndoes not display any error msg - upcoming PR -).\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes the issue by checking the command-line argument type before\r\nany code attempts to access it. Additionally, it improves the returned error\r\nmessage, changing it to:\r\n\"Invalid '-nowallet=not_a_boolean': Value must be a boolean (0/1 or false/true)\"",
